(Flat index — full Socratic explanations live in the depth-ordered Walkthrough below.)

### Orchestration (LangGraph) — the spine
- [**Typed state with field-level reducers**](#1-the-state-graph-structure-state-branching) — One `TypedDict` for the whole game; field-level reducers control merge semantics.
- [**Streaming graph updates**](#1-the-state-graph-structure-state-branching) — `graph.stream(..., stream_mode="updates")` emits one `{node: update}` per super-step.
- [**Conditional edges with a routing function**](#1-the-state-graph-structure-state-branching) — Branching is a router function plus an `add_conditional_edges` mapping.
- [**One function, two node names for fan-out**](#1-the-state-graph-structure-state-branching) — One pure read function powers two fan-out sites by being registered under two node names.
- [**Cycle tail edge**](#1-the-state-graph-structure-state-branching) — Day → Night loops via a single tail edge; the cycle counter bumps on re-entry.

### Human-in-the-loop
- [**Replay-safe interrupt placement**](#2-the-human-in-the-loop-pausing-the-graph-for-a-real-player) — `interrupt()` opens any human-facing node so resume re-runs the whole node cleanly.
