## Diagram

The compiled state graph for the playable skeleton. Solid arrows are unconditional edges; dotted arrows are conditional branches via router functions. Keep this picture handy — the Walkthrough below refers back to its parts repeatedly.

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    START([START])
    cn[collect_name]
    gr[generate_roster]
    ar[assign_roles]
    ir[introduce_roster]
    rr[reveal_role]
    fnmi[first_night_mafia_intros]
    no[night_open]
    mp[mafia_pointing]
    rnk[resolve_night_kill]
    cwn{check_win_night}
    nc[night_close]
    do[day_open]
    dt[day_turn]
    vp[vote_prompt]
    cv[collect_votes]
    rv[resolve_vote]
    cwd{check_win_day}
    dc[day_close]
    es[end_screen]
    ENDN([END])

    START --> cn --> gr --> ar --> ir --> rr --> fnmi --> no
    no -. end_screen .-> es
    no -. mafia_pointing .-> mp
    mp --> rnk --> cwn
    cwn -. end_screen .-> es
    cwn -. night_close .-> nc
    nc --> do --> dt
    dt -. vote_prompt .-> vp
    dt -. day_turn loop .-> dt
    dt -. day_close .-> dc
    vp --> cv
    cv -. collect_votes loop .-> cv
    cv -. resolve_vote .-> rv
    rv --> cwd
    cwd -. end_screen .-> es
    cwd -. day_turn .-> dt
    cwd -. day_close .-> dc
    dc -. cycle bump .-> no
    es --> ENDN
```

